==Russian==
[[Category:Russian nouns]]
===Etymology===
From Greek [[ορθός]] (straight, right, true) and [[γράμμα]] (letter, writing).

===Noun===
'''орфограмма''' (orfográmma) {{f}}

# A spelling that is in accordance with orthographic rules, usually etymological or historical rather than phonetic.
# A consistently reproducible way to represent phonomorphological features of a given language in writing, such as '''-ого''' for the Russian masculine genitive singular of adjectives, instead of the phonetic spelling '''-ава''': [[новый|нового]] (nóvəvə).

